// BUG-NEW-02 (v0.0.4): Bool as array index is NOT caught by !? ... :!
//
// Root cause: the type check "array index must be Int, got Bool" bypasses
// the RuntimeError machinery and terminates the process directly.
//
// Expected (correct behavior): !? should catch the error and print "caught".
// Actual behavior: program exits with code 1; :! block never executes.
//
// Contrast: arr[0], arr[99], 1/0 ARE all correctly caught by !?.
// See also: tests/v0.0.4_review/runtime_errors_catchable.zy

arr = [1,2,3]
!? {
    x = arr[#1]
    >> x ¶
} :! {
    >> "caught bool index" ¶
}
